The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                          Wednesday , November 4 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                            IN THE CITY
                        
	 Belgian Philip de Ridder is expected to be present in Mumbai when East Bengal take on Air India on Saturday. However, assistant coach Tushar Rakshit will still be calling the shots. De Ridder will officially take over as coach only after the team returns.                
	 Mohun Bagan will inaugurate their new football academy in Jalpaiguri on November 21. The academy will have boys between 16 and 19 years and it will be a residential and , within the age group of 16-19 years, with a budget of 10 lakhs per annum for five years.                       
	 Khalin Joshi of Bangalore took an early lead after the first round when he shot an even par round in the Faldo Series Junior Golf Championship at the RCGC Tuesday. Trishul Chinappa was in the lead till the 17th hole but was penalised a stroke for slow play. Playing steadily, Vidit Singh is in lead in the Category C after he shot 8 over 80. Tejendar Ghai has taken an early lead with 6 over 78 in Category B.                      
	 TCS defeated HT Media 3-0 in the 5-a-side mercantile football tournament, organised by the Calcutta Rangers Club Tuesday.      
	Other results: British Deputy High Commission drew DPSC 1-1; ITC District drew Park 0-0.                      
	Cricket: CK Nayudu under-22: Hyderabad vs Bengal at JU, Salt Lake from 9am      
	Soccer: CFL: George Telegraph vs Peerless SC at Khardah Stadium from 2.45pm                                                                                                                                                                       
